
About Me

I'm a developer driven by curiosity and raw creative energy. I build for the thrill of the idea — not to chase trends, but to chase insight. My projects range from toy experiments to ambitious system-level concepts like self-rewriting code and database-driven OS design.

I move fast, I follow sparks, and I finish what I start. Each build is a challenge to think sharper, design cleaner, and push deeper into what software can become. I don’t wait for perfect plans. I ship, I learn, and I move.

This isn’t about credentials. It’s about momentum — one idea at a time.

---

Areas of Expertise

Rapid Prototyping & Toy Systems
Building fast, functional prototypes to explore ideas with minimal overhead.

End-to-End Product Thinking
Taking ideas from scratch to usable tools — frontend to backend, logic to UI.
Curiosity-Driven Development
Not afraid to pivot, discard, or go deep — driven by questions, not trends.

